<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_37456175-fe84-4540-962e-9c43014e2d3e" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="VIC"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>I4P1</sptc><title id="_8ea34672-d2fe-4537-aac9-6e0c3300277a">Heated water temperature</title><archive-num>2019: VIC HP101.1</archive-num><subclause id="_2309c933-9bef-4e14-9d40-bbbc30e4eaf1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_4fdc369c-24cf-4ee3-8e08-1936d3fcabed">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The temperature of water supplied to baths and showers for use by residents must be controlled to avoid the risk of scalding whilst ensuring the stored water temperature does not encourage the growth of Legionella Bacteria.</p></subclause><callout id="_3722583f-bc4e-4116-9a11-d08969ec7cdb"><callout-type ncc-info-type="application"/><p>VIC I4P1 only applies to Class 3 and Class 9a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1435_0.4.0.xml#_d421a23a-314a-49a0-8732-395e884a7a39" id="_50e29345-88d5-4151-9644-28b3e256f550" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">residential aged care buildings</xref> and Class 9c buildings.</p></callout></clause>